        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 2.  ANNUITY CHARGE
Art. 2787.  Annuity charge
An annuity contract transferring an immovable may provide for the establishment of a charge on the immovable for the periodic payments due under the contract.  In such a case, the recipient in whose favor the annuity was established acquires a real right for periodic payments. The establishment of the annuity charge must be express and in writing.</p>
        </content>
